The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 27 June is 282,888 (32,604.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 22 June, there were 1,761 new confirmed cases (203.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 15 June, there were 1,494 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 18% (267 extra cases).
